{"title_page": "List of historical Gnutella clients", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nMany projects have attempted to use the [[Gnutella]] network, since its introduction in early 2000.  This list enumerates abandoned or discontinued projects.\n\n== List of discontinued clients ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Name || Platform || Last Release || License\n|-\n| '''CocoGnut''' || [[RISC OS]] || June 28, 2005 <ref>[http://www.alpha-programming.co.uk/software/cocognut/ CocoGnut 1.21 release]</ref> || Freeware\n|-\n| '''Gnotella''' || [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] || before March 2002 <ref>[http://www.gnutellaforums.com/gnotella-windows/9366-so-why-has-gnotella-been-discontinued.html Gnotella discontinued post]</ref> || Freeware\n|-\n| '''Mactella''' || [[Macintosh]] || December 7, 2001 <ref>[http://www.tucows.com/preview/206631 Tucows, Mactella Version 1.4.0]</ref> || Freeware\n|-\n| [[MLDonkey]] || [[Cross-platform]] || July 27, 2007 <ref>[http://sourceforge.net/forum/forum.php?forum_id=719769 MLDonkey removes Gnutella and G2 support.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090114231255/http://sourceforge.net/forum/forum.php?forum_id=719769 |date=2009-01-14 }}</ref> || [[GNU GPL]]\n|-\n| '''Mutella''' || [[Unix]] || August 26, 2004 <ref>[http://mutella.cvs.sourceforge.net/mutella/mutella/CHANGES?revision=1.8&view=markup Mutella CHANGES files on [[Sourceforge.net]] ]</ref>|| [[GPL]]\n|-\n| '''Newtella''' || [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] || December 18, 2000 <ref>[http://tucows.mundofree.com/winme/preview/156777.html Tucows, Newtella Version 1.0b3]</ref> || Freeware\n|-\n| '''PEERanha''' || [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] || April 12, 2002 <ref>[http://www.gnutellaforums.com/peeranha-windows/10398-peeranha-dead.html PEERanha developer signals the end.]</ref> || Unknown\n|-\n| [http://qtella.sourceforge.net/ Qtella] || [[Unix-like]] || May 27, 2004 <ref>[http://sourceforge.net/projects/qtella/ Qtella SourceForge.net page]</ref> || [[GNU GPL]]  \n|-\n| '''SwapNut''' || [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] || Unknown || Unknown\n|-\n| [http://www.revolutionarystuff.com/swapper/ Swapper] || [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] || ''Temporary'' due to litigation || Proprietary\n|-\n| '''ToadNode''' || [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] || October 1, 2002 <ref>[http://www.freedownloadscenter.com/Network_and_Internet/Internet_Client_Suites/Toadnode.html Free Download Center, Toadnode 3.1.3]</ref> || Freeware\n|-\n| '''XoloX''' || [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] || April 21, 2003 <ref>[http://www.gnutellaforums.com/version-information/19237-1-5-a.html XoloX version 1.5 release]</ref> || Proprietary\n|-\n|-\n| XNap || [[Java platform|Java]] || July 14, 2004 <ref>[http://sourceforge.net/projects/xnap/ Xnap SourceForge.net page]</ref>|| [[GNU GPL]]\n|}\n\n== List of former gnutella clients ==\nSoftware that still work but dropped the GNUtella protocol.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Name || Platform || Last Release || License\n|-\n| '''[[FrostWire]]'''  (since version 5 uses only BitTorrents) || [[Java (programming language)|Java]] || 6 (2015-02-18) || GNU GPL\n|-\n| '''MP3 Rocket''' (since 2011 is only a YouTube downloader) || [[Java (programming language)|Java]] || 7.3 (2015-03-02) || GNU GPL\n|-\n| '''[[iMesh]]''' (since version 6 dropped GNUtella) || [[Windows]] || 2012 || Proprietary\n|}\n\n== Additional information ==\n\n=== Mutella ===\n[[Image:Mutella-remote-0.3.9b-searches.png|thumbnail|Mutella version 0.3.9b ''remote control'' web [[graphical user interface|gui]] showing search progress.]]\n\n<!-- \n* Name - Mutella\n* Screenshot - [[Image:Mutella-0.3.9b-info.png|250px]]\n* Caption - Mutella version 0.3.9b [[text mode]] [[user interface|ui]] showing connection information\n-->\n* Developers - Max Zaitsev, Gregory Block\n* Operating system - [[UNIX]]\n* Latest release version - 0.4.5\n* Genre - [[peer to peer]]\n* License - [[gpl]]\n* Website - [http://mutella.sourceforge.net/ Mutella development site]\n\n'''Mutella''' was a [[Gnutella]] client developed by Max Zaitsev and Gregory Block. It had two [[user interface]]s, one for textmode use and another called ''remote control'', which ran on an integrated web server and was used by a [[web browser]]. The first public version of Mutella was published on October 6, 2001.\n\nThe Mutella logo was changed into a [[squid]] somewhere around version 4.1. Before this change the logo used to be an [[Ouroboros]]. There was a blue and a black version of the ouroboros logo.\n\n=== SwapNut ===\n[http://slashdot.org/articles/01/09/23/0557259.shtml Slashdot] reports that [[LimeWire]] and SwapNut used the same code.  The website was '''www.swapnut.com'''.\n\n=== XoloX ===\n'''XoloX''' {{IPAc-en|\u02c8|z|o\u028a|l|\u0252|k|s}} was a [[Gnutella]]-based [[peer-to-peer]] [[file sharing]] application for [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]]. It advertised having no [[spyware]], [[adware]], or [[hijackware]]. However, upon installation, it prompted the user to install programs suspected to be of that kind.  Also, [[Microsoft Anti-Spyware]] detected adware programs when you started to install the program.\n\n==== XoloX links====\n* '''www.xolox.nl''' was the Official Website. Dead since June 2007.\n*[http://www.mp3newswire.net/stories/2002/xoloxreview.html Review: Xolox]\n\n==See also==\n* [[Abandonware]]\n* [[Comparison of Gnutella software]]\n\n== References ==\n* [http://www.gnutellaforums.com/discontinued-gnutella-client-forums/ Discontinued Gnutella Clients]\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n<!--\nSee http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Footnotes for an explanation of how to generate footnotes using the <ref> and </ref> tags and the tag below.\n-->\n\n{{Gnutella|Gnutella clients{{!}}*}}\n\n[[Category:Gnutella clients]]\n[[Category:Lists of software|Gnutella clients, historical]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nMany projects have attempted to use the [[Gnutella]] network, since its introduction in early 2000.  This list enumerates abandoned or dis